' @id(CMP-SESSION-CLI)
' @desc(CMP-SESSION-CLI, "The `mdd context` entry point: mdd-cli Commands::Context calls Project::session_context() in mdd-core and prints the whole-map TOC plus the freshness verdict. Reuses CMP-TRACE-GATE's map_status() for the freshness half rather than re-implementing it, and reads .mdd/map for the TOC half. Exit 0 always — a brief, not a gate.")
' @id(CMP-INIT-HOOK)
' @desc(CMP-INIT-HOOK, "mdd init wires the SessionStart hook: a JSON-structured idempotent merge of DOM-SESSION-HOOK into .claude/settings.json (the analogue of write_managed_block for JSON), plus mdd clean removing exactly that entry. Re-init never duplicates the hook; user-authored hooks and permissions already in settings.json are preserved.")
' @id(CMP-ENTRYPOINT-DIRECTIVE)
' @desc(CMP-ENTRYPOINT-DIRECTIVE, "The diagrams-first reading-order text mdd init injects into the CLAUDE.md and AGENTS.md managed blocks (templates::claude_entrypoint / agents_entrypoint), including the AGENTS.md line telling Codex and other agents to run `mdd context` manually at session start since they cannot auto-fire a hook. Realizes USE-DIAGRAMS-FIRST.")
' Objective ownership for agent session bootstrap (cycle 0014).
title Agent session bootstrap — ownership (objective)

actor "Agent" as Agent <<missing>>

component "mdd context\n(CMP-SESSION-CLI)" as Cli
component "mdd init / mdd clean\nSessionStart hook merge\n(CMP-INIT-HOOK)" as Init
component "entrypoint directive\nCLAUDE.md + AGENTS.md\n(CMP-ENTRYPOINT-DIRECTIVE)" as Directive
component "Project::map_status\n(CMP-TRACE-GATE, reused)" as Gate
folder "whole-map\n.mdd/map" as Map
folder "settings\n.claude/settings.json" as Settings

Agent --> Cli : mdd context
Agent --> Directive : reads at session start
Cli --> Gate : map_status() freshness
Cli --> Map : TOC (concepts by kind)
Init --> Settings : merge SessionStart hook (idempotent)
Init --> Directive : inject managed block

note bottom of Gate
  Freshness reuses the cycle-0013 git+syn engine;
  the baseline is DOM-MAP-BASELINE (derived from git).
end note
@enduml
